The owners of the ‘Cityzen’ team are close to acquiring the Italian team as their property, according to The Athletic. Palermo would be the umpteenth club owned by the ‘City group’, along with teams like Girona, Melbourne City FC, Troyes, New York City FC and Yokohama Marinos The Manchester City brand is spreading around the world at an unstoppable rate. And not only because of the successes of the team, but because of the power of the City Football Group , which will extend its ownership to a new club in Italy , Palermo FC . The whole of Series B will be acquired by the ‘holding’ immediately, according to ‘The Athletic’.   Ronaldo rules out Old Trafford exit     Mourinho reflects on Roma renaissance     David Beckham hunts Vidal for Inter Miami   Founded in 2013 , the group is 78% owned by the Abu Dhabi United Group and was led by Ferran Soriano with the aim of creating a global business entity. With its expansion to ‘Calcio’, the group would acquire a history of the competition in low hours after going bankrupt in 2019 . Palermo was refunded that year starting from the bottom, in Serie D , and three years later they are already in the second tier of Italian football. Now they can afford to dream of returning to Serie A. Dario Mirri, owner of the Sicilian team, warned in statements to ‘La Gazzetta dello Sport’ that ‘whoever comes will have to be persuaded that we are more than a satellite club’ . The team broke attendance records in Serie C with more than 30,000 spectators in its play-off match, and its social mass has proven to have enough level to be at the top.